    <h1>THE&#xAD;ATRE</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200918/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-18"><time>2020-09-18</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Self-Imag­i­na­tion: Sofia Nin x Is­ma­hairie Pu­tra</p>
    <p>Held in con­junc­tion with Bu­lan Ba­hasa (Malay Lan­guage Month), the Cipta Cita (loosely trans­lated as “in­spir­ing cre­ativ­ity”) se­ries puts the spot­light on modern Malay mu­sic-mak­ing artists from the re­gion. Radin Sofia Azrindawan­i, bet­ter known as Sofia Nin, launched her first col­lec­tion of po­ems Puisi Ber­an­takan at the Asean Lit­er­ary Fes­ti­val in 2014. Is­ma­hairie Pu­tra is a mu­si­cian who has per­formed with the Sin­ga­pore Malay Orches­tra since 1995.</p>
    <p>WHERE: View the live stream from Es­planade WHEN: Sun, 8pm (avail­able on­line till Sept 30) AD­MIS­SION: Free INFO: es­planade.com</p>
    <p>Rindu Jadi Lagu (A Song Of Long­ing) – Main Tulis Group</p>
    <p>This show, also part of the Cipta Cinta se­ries, is about three friends who re­unite as phase two of the re­open­ing be­gins. One wants to ser­e­nade her boyfriend. An­other wants to start a pod­cast. The third just wants every­one to stop wor­ry­ing about her. Rindu Jadi Lagu is writer Sab’s at­tempt at cap­tur­ing the ups and downs of these un­cer­tain times and how they af­fect the work­ing class. A found­ing mem­ber of the Main Tulis Group, Sin­ga­pore’s first Malay play­wright col­lec­tive, Sab is al­ways look­ing for op­por­tu­ni­ties to ex­plore the in­ter­sec­tions of race, re­li­gion, class, gen­der and sex­u­al­ity. This show is per­formed in Malay and con­tains strong lan­guage. Viewer dis­cre­tion is ad­vised.</p>
    <p>WHERE: View the live stream from Es­planade WHEN: Tomorrow, 8pm (avail­able on­line till Sept 30)</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION: Free INFO: es­planade.com</p>
    <p>Sto­ry­telling Per­for­mance: Sto­ries Of Courage</p>
    <p>(For 16 years and above)</p>
    <p>Lis­ten to an eclec­tic mix of sto­ries – from folk­tales to per­sonal en­coun­ters – in this event by Sto­ryLab, which was formed in 2009 by a group of sto­ry­tellers as a plat­form for its mem­bers to hone their art in per­for­mance sto­ry­telling. For the first time, Sto­ryLab will hold a free per­for­mance on Zoom for adult au­di­ences .</p>
    <p>WHERE: View it on­line via Zoom WHEN: Tomorrow, 7.30pm AD­MIS­SION: Free; reg­is­tra­tion is re­quired INFO: art­sre­pub­lic.sg</p>


